_**1. PROBLEM STATEMENT**_
Fake news is spreading rapidly through social media platforms like WhatsApp, Instagram, and online websites.
It becomes difficult for users to identify whether a news article is real or fake.
This leads to:
Misinformation
Panic in society
Wrong decision-making
There is a need for a simple automated system that can classify news content accurately.

 Objective:

To build a Machine Learning model that can detect fake news based on text input.


2. SCOPE OF THE PROJECT
Can be used for basic fake news detection
Works on:
a)Politics news
b)Science news
c)Social media rumors
d)Can be extended to:
e)Real-time news verification


Integration with websites/apps
Helps in:
Learning NLP (Natural Language Processing)
Understanding Machine Learning concepts

 Limitations:

Works on small dataset (not real-world scale)
Accuracy depends on training data quality


3. TARGET USERS
a)Students (for learning AI/ML concepts)
b)Social media users
c)News readers
d)Beginners in data science
e)Teachers for demonstration purposes


 4. FEATURES OF THE PROJECT
🔹 Core Features
Accepts user input news text
Classifies news as:
✅ Real
❌ Fake
🔹 Machine Learning Features
Uses TF-IDF Vectorization
Uses Multinomial Naive Bayes algorithm
Trained on multi-domain dataset
🔹 Data Processing Features
Converts text to lowercase
Removes punctuation
Removes stopwords (like “is”, “the”)
🔹 Performance Features
Displays model accuracy
Handles unseen input data
Fast prediction
🔹 User Interaction Features
Interactive console-based system
Continuous input until user exits
Simple and beginner-friendly
